yingyinNormal.en: Typically, your body has a number of genetic mechanisms to control how fast your cells divide.
yingyinNormal.zh: 通常来说，你的身体有一些控制细胞分裂速度的遗传机制。

yingyinNormal.en: Cancer is like a car crash. Your body typically regulates the speed at which your cells divide.
yingyinNormal.zh: 癌症就像一场车祸。通常，你的身体调节着细胞分裂的速度。

yingyinNormal.en: They're good jobs that typically pay about 15% more than the national average.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这些工作岗位待遇丰厚，工资比全国平均水平高出15%。

yingyinNormal.en: These include areas typically associated with social cognition, attention, and cognitive control.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这些区块基本上都和社会认知注意力以及认知控制有关。

yingyinNormal.en: Step two is to encounter the problems that stand in the way of getting to your goals. These problems are typically painful.
yingyinNormal.zh: 第二步直面挡在你追寻路上的问题。这些问题一般很难办。

yingyinNormal.en: How many people in the audience have the last name Resnick like me? Raise your hand. Anybody? Nobody. Typically, there's one or two.
yingyinNormal.zh: 观众里有多少人跟我同一个姓，雷斯尼克？请举手。有人是吗？ 没有。明显，有一两个。

yingyinNormal.en: I learned that while most everyone expects the future to be a slightly modified version of the present, it is typically very different.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我也明白了虽然每个人觉得未来只是稍有不同的现在版本，但事实是非常不同的。

yingyinNormal.en: We're typically 8 feet off the ground traveling 120 to 150 miles an hour, using GPS navigation that will give us guidance to within about 1 or 2 feet.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们几乎离地只有8英尺，每小时飞行120到150英里，全球定位仪会为我们提供导航，精度能达到1到2英尺。

yingyinNormal.en: Yes, there is. Oh, here's a fun fact. Ketchup started out as a general term for sauce, typically made of mushrooms or fish brine with herbs and spices.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是滴。有个好玩的事儿，起初，番茄酱是酱汁的总称，特别是那些加了草本植物和香料的蘑菇或腌鱼。

yingyinNormal.en: On one hand, learning very negative, highly immoral information about someone typically has a stronger impact than learning very positive, highly moral information.
yingyinNormal.zh: 一方面，知道关于某人非常负面、非常不道德的信息，基本上会有更强的影响，相对于得知某人有非常正面、道德的信息。

yingyinNormal.en: Guys, this is a log scale. You don't typically see lines that go up like that. So the worldwide capacity to sequence human genomes is something like 50,000 to 100,000 human genomes this year.
yingyinNormal.zh: 各位，这是个对数尺度，你不会常看到趋势像那样上升，所以世界范围内可进行人类基因组测序的能力，今年大概是五万到十万人类基因组。

sense_info_list.en: used when you are giving an average or usual example of a particular thing

examination_example.sentence: Jasmine Bina explains, "<highlight>Typically</highlight>, luxury brands rally around exclusivity to protect their business interests, namely intellectual property and preservation of brand equity (资产)."
examination_example.sentence_trans: Jasmine Bina解释道，“通常，奢侈品牌会排他性地团结起来，以保护其商业利益，即保护知识产权和品牌资产。”

examination_example.sentence: Instead, they receive a fixed rate, which is <highlight>typically</highlight> about $825 for a standard four-hour vocal session.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 取而代之的是，他们会收到固定费率，对于一个标准的四小时人声会话，通常约为825美元。

examination_example.sentence: The Grand Tourist was <highlight>typically</highlight> a young man with a thorough grounding in Greek and Latin literature as well as some leisure time.
examination_example.sentence_trans: “大游客”(Grand Tourist)通常是年轻人，有扎实的希腊和拉丁文学方面的基础，并且有一些休闲时间。
